law.text:
After notice and opportunity for a hearing, the Commissioner may suspend or revoke a license if the Commissioner finds that the licensee:
has violated any provision of this title;
has failed to maintain the standards required under this title for the issuance of an initial license;
is insolvent;
has liabilities that exceed its assets;
has engaged in a fraudulent or deceptive act; or
has entered into a service contract the form of which has not been approved by the Commissioner.
